==English==

===Etymology===
From the Greek [[Αβραάμ]] (''Avraám''), through Late Latin; from the Hebrew [[אברהם|אַבְרָהָם]] ('''Abrāhām''). Possibly compounded from [[אב|אָב]] (av) 'father' + [[המון]] (hamon) 'multitude' (father of a multitude of nations).

===Proper noun===
'''Abraham'''

# A male [[given name]] of biblical origin, meaning "father/leader of many".
# A character in the [[Old Testament]].

